      <section eId="sec_15_12_60">
        <num>15-12-60</num>
        <content>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 3821; Code 1868, § 3841; Code 1873, § 3906; Code 1882, § 3906; Ga. L. 1887, p. 53, § 1; Penal Code 1895, § 811; Penal Code 1910, § 811; Code 1933, § 59-201; Ga. L. 1953, Nov.-Dec. Sess., p. 284, § 3; Ga. L. 1973, p. 726, § 1; Ga. L. 1976, p. 438, § 6; Ga. L. 1977, p. 341, § 1; Ga. L. 1982, p. 779, §§ 1, 2; Ga. L. 1983, p. 3, § 12; Ga. L. 2011, p. 59, § 1-26/HB 415; Ga. L. 2012, p. 173, § 3-3/HB 665; Ga. L. 2015, p. 693, § 1A-1/HB 233; Ga. L. 2018, p. 1112, § 15/SB 365.)</p>
          <p>The 2015 amendment,
      effective July 1, 2015, substituted the present provisions of subsection (c) for the former provisions, which read: "Any person who has been convicted of a felony in a state or federal court who has not had his or her civil rights restored and any person who has been judicially determined to be mentally incompetent shall not be eligible to serve as a grand juror."; and added subsection (d). See editor's note for applicability.</p>
          <p>The 2018 amendment,
      effective May 8, 2018, part of an Act to revise, modernize, and correct the Code, substituted "Article 4 of Chapter 3 of Title 42" for "Article 5 of Chapter 8 of Title 42" in the middle of paragraph (c)(3).</p>
        </content>
